NAME
lxcu.conf - Configuration file for the lxcu suite.
DESCRIPTION
lxcu.conf contains one line for each parameter (Key / Value pair).
FILES
lxcu.conf	The parameters are as follows:-

dist=	default distribution

rel=	default release

arch=	default architecture

contlocation=	The location of the container files

bridge= 	The name of the bridge network interfcae if there is one,
otherwise leave blank

ethernetprefix=		The prefix of the ethernet interfaces on the machine, it
is usually eth or enp

vni=	The default virtual network interface

gitemail=	Set up a git email config parameter

gitname=	Set up a git name config parameter

localelang=	Locale setting for LANG

localekeymap=	Keymap setting for v/c

localex11keymap=	X11 keymap setting

The file is stored in an etc directory. The exact location depends on the method
of installation but for Autotools installations on Linux this is likely to
be /usr/local/etc/lxcu/lxcu.conf.
